tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured laboratory values are within normal limits. Glycemic control (HbA1c, glucose) is adequate, and renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are normal. No laboratory abnormalities detected; no acute or chronic issues apparent from these results. Recommend routine follow-up as clinically indicated.
